--- Volkswagen Restorations USA
<volksfix(-at-)bellsouth.net> wrote:
> You need to check the oil pressure with a manual
> gauge. I would not run the
> engine until you do so. If you have good pressure,
> it is most likely a bad
> sending unit, or a shorted to ground sending unit
> wire. I would use a
> factory sending unit if you have to replace it, as
> the pressure ranges on
> the aftermarket can be off quite a bit.
>     Good luck.
> 
